00:17:08,500 --> 00:17:12,350
Is that so? Well, gee, maybe the old
Flanders-mobile could use...

229
00:17:14,923 --> 00:17:18,257
Wow, lucky I always keep a Bible
close to my heart...

230
00:17:21,889 --> 00:17:26,218
Lucky I was wearing this extra-large
piece of the true cross today.

231
00:17:26,769 --> 00:17:28,227
I think I'll go inside.

232
00:17:30,439 --> 00:17:32,630
What keeps doing that?

233
00:17:32,274 --> 00:17:36,580
I told you we should've bought more
than three bullets. Let's just grab him.

234
00:17:36,570 --> 00:17:37,945
Hey!

235
00:17:39,990 --> 00:17:43,110
But wait. You can't kill me
for being Krusty. I'm not him.

236
00:17:43,327 --> 00:17:45,782
- I'm Homer Simpson.
- The same Homer Simpson who...

237
00:17:45,954 --> 00:17:48,280
...crashed his car through the wall
of our club?

238
00:17:48,707 --> 00:17:51,281
Actually, my name is Barney.
Yeah, Barney Gumble.

239
00:17:51,460 --> 00:17:54,794
The same Barney Gumble
who keeps taking pictures of my sister?

240
00:17:55,500 --> 00:17:56,749
Actually, my real name is...

241
00:17:57,216 --> 00:17:59,125
Think, Krusty, think. Joe Valachi.

242
00:17:59,343 --> 00:18:03,910
Same Joe Valachi who squealed to the
Senate committee about organized crime?

243
00:18:03,305 --> 00:18:05,464
- Benedict Arnold.
- The same Benedict Arnold...

244
00:18:05,641 --> 00:18:08,511
...who plotted to surrender
West Point to the hated British?

245
00:18:11,981 --> 00:18:15,848
I am so glad I had
a chance to meet you...

246
00:18:16,680 --> 00:18:20,694
...before we did this, Krusty,
because I am a great fan.

247
00:18:21,240 --> 00:18:23,363
Don Vittorio Dimaggio.

248
00:18:23,534 --> 00:18:25,242
Krusty the Clown.

249
00:18:25,828 --> 00:18:28,366
Sorry I have to do this, Krusty.

250
00:18:31,333 --> 00:18:33,456
I cannot do it.

251
00:18:33,669 --> 00:18:38,746
To murder a funnyman
of such genius would be a crime.

252
00:18:39,550 --> 00:18:41,210
Tell you what, Krusty.

253
00:18:41,385 --> 00:18:45,881
Do for me my favorite trick, where you
ride the little bike through the loop...

254
00:18:46,560 --> 00:18:49,757
...and I will let you live.
- But I've never been able to do the...

255
00:18:50,190 --> 00:18:53,518
Hey, how about if I squirt you
in the face with my boutonnière? Okay.

256
00:18:55,315 --> 00:18:59,160
- I'll never be able to do this trick. Never.
- Go. Go.

257
00:19:01,780 --> 00:19:04,568
Hey. I'm doing it. I'm doing it.

258
00:19:04,783 --> 00:19:07,155
I'm the greatest clown in the world.

259
00:19:16,170 --> 00:19:21,793
The fact that you did not do the trick
well is the biggest insult of all.

260
00:19:22,509 --> 00:19:23,920
Hey, guys. I came to...

261
00:19:25,471 --> 00:19:28,637
Oh, you got a deadly game of
cat and mouse going. I'll come back.

262
00:19:29,975 --> 00:19:32,549
I'm seeing double here.
Four Krustys.

263
00:19:32,770 --> 00:19:37,562
Krusty. Oh, thanks. Thanks a lot.
You came here to save me.

264
00:19:37,775 --> 00:19:40,266
Yeah. That's what I did.

265
00:19:40,486 --> 00:19:45,611
My apologies to you. I almost
made a grievous error.

266
00:19:45,783 --> 00:19:48,404
- Goodbye, Krusty.
- Wait.

267
00:19:48,619 --> 00:19:52,367
He can't kill anybody if he doesn't
know which one's the real Krusty.

268
00:19:56,377 --> 00:19:57,835
I am confused.

269
00:19:58,879 --> 00:20:01,797
- Good one, Krusty.
- Oh, crap.

270
00:20:02,700 --> 00:20:04,878
Because of that
disrespectful display...

271
00:20:05,520 --> 00:20:07,258
...I shall now kill both of you.

272
00:20:08,597 --> 00:20:13,930
Unless you both go
through the loop together.

273
00:20:22,444 --> 00:20:25,529
I can't see, you idiot.
Take your hands off my eyes.

274
00:20:43,590 --> 00:20:45,464
- Hey.
- Not bad.

275
00:20:46,510 --> 00:20:47,843
Without the loop, it is nothing.

276
00:21:03,360 --> 00:21:05,567
Yeah, Krustys!

277
00:21:07,310 --> 00:21:12,985
Grazie. Grazie. You have brought
great joy to this old Italian stereotype.

278
00:21:13,203 --> 00:21:17,710
- No, no, Don Vittorio. You're not...
- Yes, I am. I know it. I am.

279
00:21:17,291 --> 00:21:21,390
- Anyway, thank you, Krusty.
- Oh, you're welcome.

280
00:21:21,253 --> 00:21:25,121
- So we're even now, huh?
- No, we just won't kill you.

281
00:21:25,299 --> 00:21:27,291
But you still owe us the money.

282
00:21:28,930 --> 00:21:30,798
- Forty-eight dollars.
- Here's 50.

283
00:21:31,130 --> 00:21:34,464
And 2, your change.
And we thank you.

